<!-- <title>Previo a la unidad</title> -->
<title>Exploración</title>
<!-- <title component="metadata">Alineado con <xref ref="graVV-uniYY-secZZ" text="title"/></title> -->
<!-- <title component="metadata">Alineado con <xref ref="lec-VVVVVV" text="title"/></title> -->

<statement>
  <p>Decide si cada fracción es un número entero. Explica o muestra cómo razonaste.</p>
  <ol cols="3">
    <li>
      <p><m>\frac{100}{2}</m></p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p><m>\frac{100}{3}</m></p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p><m>\frac{100}{4}</m></p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p><m>\frac{100}{6}</m></p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p><m>\frac{100}{8}</m></p>
    </li>
  </ol>
</statement>

<solution>
  <p>[++++++++++++++++++++]</p>
  <ol>
    <li>
      <p>Yes. Each 2 halves make a whole so 100 halves make 50.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>No. Three thirds make a whole so 99 thirds is 33 and then here is one extra third.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>Yes. Each 4 fourths make a whole so 40 fourths make 10, 80 fourths make 20, and 100 fourths make 25.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>No. Six sixths make a whole so 60 sixths make 10, 36 more make 6 more and then there are 4 extra sixths.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>No. Eight eighths make a whole so 80 eighths make 10, 16 more make 2 more and there are 4 extra eighths.</p>
    </li>
  </ol>
</solution>

</exercise>
